Description:
Family Expanse with Scope to Enhance!
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Set on a wonderfully deep block of land (Approx 750m2), this two-storey residence has been loved and maintained by the one family since new, and now provides an exceptional opportunity to modernize and personalize or explore the property's unique redevelopment potential (STCA). Immaculately presented throughout, the home's light-filled interior comprises five main bedrooms (extra-large master with private ensuite), study/sixth bedroom, main family bathroom and additional powder room. Add to this a spacious front lounge and adjoining dining room leading through to the family/meals area and updated kitchen complete with tiled splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Other highlights include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, alarm system, security shutters and solid hardwood floors, large laundry and under-stair storeroom. Step outside to discover a surprisingly large backyard with undercover pergola/entertaining area, established fruit trees and huge four-car garage via gated side driveway. Conveniently positioned, it's walking distance to local parks and playgrounds, Milleara Shopping Centre, close to public transport, popular primary and secondary schools as well as easy freeway access.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you.

Description:
Grand Proportions
Nestled away in a hidden community is a piece of paradise completed with lake and boardwalk.
Split across 3 levels this home is sure to impress, the ground floor has a double garage with internal access to a large laundry and into the entry with a good sized bedroom and large ensuite. Take the stairs to the first level and prepare to be amazed, panoramic views of the lake from every window.
A large sleek kitchen with island bench flows onto the open plan meals and living room, complete with a enclosed Balcony and powder room.
The second level is for sleeping with a large master including ensuite and walk in robe and private balcony, an additional 2 bedrooms with large BIR and family bathroom with separate bath and walk in shower.
Split systems to all bedrooms as well as the living area, secure and good sized rear yard.
Beautifully presented home call today for your inspection.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
With its open-design interior, enhanced features and substantial surrounds, this single-level home is ready to enjoy along with terrific opportunities for those looking to extend, renew or possibly redevelop in the future (STCA) - all in one of Keilor East's most popular pockets. Beyond the established front garden and attractive rendered facade, the home's current floorplan comprises three double bedrooms (all with built-in robes) together with an updated central bathroom. Adding to its immediate appeal is a light-filled and versatile open lounge/dining area accompanied by a well-appointed kitchen complete with dishwasher. Other features of the home include ducted heating and refrigerated cooling, alarm system, solid hardwood floors, security shutters and a full-size laundry with linen cupboards. Step outside to appreciate the size and scope of its sunny backyard including two handy storage sheds, plus the added advantage of a gated side driveway (remote-controlled) for secure two-car off-street parking. A short stroll to the open spaces of Rosehill Park, Phillip Road/Buckley Street buses and Milleara Shopping Centre, it's also close to popular primary and secondary schools (including PEGS and St Bernard's College), as well as easy freeway access.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you.

A Family Prize On A Massive Block
Nestled in a prized cul-de-sac on an impressively proportioned allotment measuring approximately 1000m2, this immediately inviting three bedroom plus study, two bathroom residence offers enduring family and lifestyle appeal. Unfolding over two spacious levels, a cleverly zoned layout includes welcoming living room, warmed by a feature brick open fireplace, and central family/dining areas set off by a soaring cathedral ceiling and ambient natural light. Sliding doors provide easy access to a paved alfresco entertaining zone, while a massive backyard offers endless space for kids' activities and scope for future home improvements (STCA). A bright and open kitchen/meals area comprises 900mm gas/electric stove, Smeg dishwasher, plentiful cabinetry, pantry and breakfast bar. Comfortable accommodation is provided by three double bedrooms, including private master with balcony, ensuite, walk-in/built-in-robes and adjoining mezzanine retreat. Highlighted by family bathroom, laundry/storage, ducted heating, split-system air conditioners, semi-circular driveway and side drive to covered entry/carport and double garage. A short distance from schools, parklands, shopping centres and freeways.

Description:
Aspirational Indoor / Outdoor Lifestyle of Elegance and Versatility
***this property is available for inspection by appointment-Please contact us to arrange a suitable time****
Surrounded by landscaped gardens on vast 1100sqm+ allotment, this imposing family residence provides an exceptional environment of uncompromised quality and floorplan flexibility complemented by a spectacular resort-style poolside entertaining area. Situated in one of Keilor East's premier pockets, the home itself showcases an extra-large master bedroom with WIR and private ensuite, three additional bedrooms (all with BIRs) and three further bathrooms. Along with a home office including integrated workstation, the home also boasts a grand lounge with cathedral ceilings, formal dining room, dedicated theatre room and central living area leading through to the timber-cabinet kitchen/meals with breakfast bar, gas cooktop, double oven and double dishwasher. Other stand-out features include ducted heating and refrigerated cooling, additional ceiling fans (all bedrooms), alarm and CCTV, solar power (14 panels), family-sized laundry, excellent storage options throughout and oversized double garage with internal entry and drive-through option. The sensational enclosed al-fresco area includes a mains-connected BBQ and is ideal for all-seasons entertaining, plus an enormous backyard with a fully-automated tiled pool and spa, resort-style landscaped surrounds, 3 x 3000L watertanks and multi-zone irrigation system. Walking distance to Rosehill Park, Steele Creek trails and riverside parkland, it also offers close proximity to primary and secondary schools (including St Bernard's College and PEGS), as well as Buckley Street buses and Milleara Shopping Centre.

A perfect choice for first-time buyers and investors alike, this lovely, established home comprises of three generously sized bedrooms with built-in robes, formal lounge, a central bathroom with separate toilet and a hall with ample cupboard space.
The floorplan is completed with a massive lounge and dining area which flows through to the bright kitchen overlooking the backyard and entertaining area.
Other features include ducted heating, evaporative cooling, pergola, a large shed which can be used as a workshop and a huge double garage which can also be used as an ultimate man cave and rumpus.
Situated in a fantastic location with easy access to local shopping centres, schools, transport and all amenities.
Don't miss out! Call today for more information or to make an appointment for your private inspection.

https://www.facebook.com/flocarreon.areaspecialist/

Description:
Easy-Living Style with Flair and Flexibility
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Set in a blissfully quiet yet enviably convenient Niddrie neighbourhood, this two-storey townhouse is sure to impress with its versatile floorplan, quality inclusions and abundance of natural light throughout. Low-maintenance perfection, the home's flawlessly presented interior comprises a large downstairs master bedroom with its own private ensuite, together two additional upstairs bedrooms, main central bathroom and third WC. Spacious and versatile, the open-plan living/dining area is accompanied by a well-appointed kitchen with stone benchtops/breakfast bar, tiled splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Along with ducted heating and split-system air conditioning (both levels), the home also includes an alarm system, polished timber floors, laundry, under-stair storeroom and mirrored robes to all bedrooms. Step outside to enjoy the wonderfully wide entertainers' courtyard complete with extensive decking, integrated lighting and high fences for added privacy, plus rear access into the remote-control double garage. Ideally located walking distance to the best of Niddrie including Keilor Road trams, cafes and restaurants, vibrant shopping centre, as well as primary and secondary schools and easy access to the Calder Freeway.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
SOLD by Team Marwan
Spacious and stylish, this 2-bedroom plus study home presents the ideal living arrangement for discerning families while professionals and investors will appreciate its undeniable appeal. Quality living is assured with this home, offering all the low maintenance features for a stress-free lifestyle. Serenely secluded in a prized Niddrie pocket, close to schools, cafes, shopping centres, parks and freeways. This property truly stands out from the townhouses you have seen. You must come and see for yourself!
PROPERTY SPECIFICATIONS:
- Brick veneer and rendered Townhouse. Built in 2020 approx.
- Land size 210m2 approx. Building size of 17sq approx.
- KITCHEN: Timber 2-tone soft closing cabinetry with 40mm Calcutta benchtops, waterfall edging to breakfast bench and pendant lighting. S/S Smeg appliances including dishwasher, double kitchen sink, black chrome tapware, pantry and cupboard space, finished with hardwood engineered flooring
- MEALS: Open plan area with hardwood engineered timber flooring
- LOUNGE: Open plan area with built-in shelving nook, gas fireplace, and rear access to courtyard. Finished with hardwood engineered flooring
- 2nd LIVING/STUDY: Study/office area or 2nd living zone with hardwood engineered flooring
- BEDROOMS: 2 large bedrooms with robes and carpeted flooring. Master with 2-way access to central bathroom and pendant lighting
- BATHROOM: 2-way bathroom with 900mm shower, separate bathtub, single vanity and cupboard, black chrome tapware, combined toilet and floor to ceiling tiles
- 2nd BATHROOM: 1200mm shower, single vanity and cupboard, combined toilet area and floor to ceiling tiles
- LAUNDRY: Separate area with single trough and rear access
- HEAT/COOL: Reverse cycle ducted heating and cooling PLUS a stunning gas log fireplace
- OUTDOORS: Decked courtyard with landscaped gardens, garden beds and lawn area
- ADDITIONAL: Security alarm system with video intercom. High ceilings, LED lighting, gas HWS, timber staircase and frosted glass to some areas
- PARKING: Single remote garage, rear and internal access PLUS car space for additional car
- POTENTIAL RENT: $600- $620 p/w approx.
- ZONING: General Residential Zone - Schedule 1
- MUNICIPALITY: City of Moonee Valley
LOCATION BENEFITS:
- Close to schools including St Bernard's Catholic Boys College, Penleigh & Essendon Grammar, Ave Maria College, kinder gardens, childcare and Essendon Fields DFO and Keilor Road shopping precinct
- Near Essendon, Glenbervie & Strathmore train station. Steele Creek Trail
- Located only 15km's from CBD with terrific Calder, Ring Road and airport access plus Milleara Rd
PREFERRED SALE TERMS:
DEPOSIT:
- 10%
SETTLEMENT:
- 30/45/60 days
